âœ… What is a Nested Dictionary in Python?
A nested dictionary is a dictionary inside another dictionary.
ðŸ‘‰ Structure:
{
   "key1": {
        "subkey1": value,
        "subkey2": value
   }
}

âœ… Simple Example
student = {
    "name": "Rakesh",
    "marks": {
        "math": 90,
        "science": 85
    }
}
print(student["marks"]["math"])   # 90

Explanation:
student â†’ main dictionary
marks â†’ nested dictionary
math â†’ key inside nested dictionary

âœ… Real DevOps Example (Server Inventory)
inventory = {
    "web1": {
        "ip": "192.168.1.10",
        "os": "Linux",
        "status": "running"
    },
    "db1": {
        "ip": "192.168.1.20",
        "os": "Linux",
        "status": "stopped"
    }
}
print(inventory["web1"]["ip"])

âœ… Loop Through Nested Dictionary
for server, details in inventory.items():
    print(f"\nServer: {server}")
    for key, value in details.items():
        print(f"{key} : {value}")
Output:
Server: web1
ip : 192.168.1.10
os : Linux
status : running

âœ… Multi-Level Nested Dictionary
infrastructure = {
    "production": {
        "web": {
            "web1": {"ip": "10.0.0.1"},
            "web2": {"ip": "10.0.0.2"}
        },
        "db": {
            "db1": {"ip": "10.0.0.10"}
        }
    },
    "staging": {
        "web": {
            "stag-web1": {"ip": "192.168.0.5"}
        }
    }
}

âœ… Access Deep Values
print(infrastructure["production"]["web"]["web1"]["ip"])
Output:
10.0.0.1

âœ… Loop Through Multi-Level Dictionary
for env, roles in infrastructure.items():
    print(f"\nEnvironment: {env}")
    for role, servers in roles.items():
        print(f"  Role: {role}")
        for server, config in servers.items():
            print(f"    {server} -> {config['ip']}")

âœ… Modify Nested Dictionary
Update value
inventory["web1"]["status"] = "restarting"
Add new key
inventory["web1"]["cpu"] = "70%"
